<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    fk-002-validate.xml — RDR-156 P0.3 (bead nexus-70r3c.3)

    Completes the fk-002 collection-registry FK spine by VALIDATEing the five
    NOT VALID FKs that fk-002-collection-registry.xml (P0.2, nexus-70r3c.2)
    added in the deliberately-deferred-validation shape:

      chunks_384_collection_fk        FK (tenant_id, collection)
      chunks_768_collection_fk        FK (tenant_id, collection)
      chunks_1024_collection_fk       FK (tenant_id, collection)
      chash_index_collection_fk       FK (tenant_id, physical_collection)
      topic_assignments_collection_fk FK (tenant_id, source_collection) — nullable, ON UPDATE CASCADE

    World-block lifted 2026-06-21: the gate predicate (RDR-153 migrate-all completes
    with summary.total_failed==0) is SATISFIED — prod migrate-all report
    migration-c67ae289 (2026-06-11, total_failed=0, total_written=782159). This is
    the deferred-VALIDATE half of RDR-156 P0; the sibling of RDR-164 P1b
    (fk-003-validate.xml), which validated the OTHER five collection FKs.

    Why this is a SEPARATE changelog from P0.2 (same rationale as the fk-003 sibling):
    VALIDATE CONSTRAINT must not sit on the implementation critical path, and it has a
    hard data prerequisite that P0.2 does not — the P0.2 mandatory-registration guard
    for these tables only takes effect once P0.2 DEPLOYS. Any production write to
    chunks_*/chash_index/topic_assignments between the RDR-153 migrate-all run and the
    P0.2 deploy had NO registration guard, so it may have created a row referencing an
    unregistered collection. NOT VALID skipped retroactive validation of those rows;
    VALIDATE CONSTRAINT does NOT — it errors loudly on any such orphan.

    Therefore this changelog does TWO things, in order:

      1. fk-002-6-reconcile: re-run the idempotent STUB-REGISTER backfill (the same
         five INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING statements fk-002-0 ran) against
         CURRENT data. This catches the gap-window rows: every collection name still
         referenced by a child table but not yet registered is stub-registered now, so
         the subsequent VALIDATE has a valid parent for it. No-data-loss arm: the INSERT
         is unconditional over DISTINCT child values, so after it every non-null
         referenced (tenant_id, collection) has a parent.

         The Q5 "DELETE genuinely-orphaned" arm (b) is deliberately NOT implemented here,
         and unlike the fk-003 sibling it should NOT be: fk-002 tables (chunks_*,
         chash_index, topic_assignments) are the PRIMARY vector-serving layer, where an
         orphan chunk is real data, not lifecycle debris — deleting it would be data loss.
         Stub-register + defer cleanup to the deleteCollection cascade (RDR-164 P2) is the
         correct no-data-loss choice. (Follow-up bead nexus-ht7yq tracks arm (b) for the
         fk-003 LIFECYCLE tables only — dangling annotations/queue rows — and is NOT in
         scope for fk-002.) topic_assignments contributes
         only non-null, non-empty source_collection values (null rows escape the FK via
         MATCH SIMPLE); an empty-string (non-null) source_collection is therefore a
         stub-unsatisfiable orphan that — by design — makes VALIDATE FAIL LOUD rather
         than admit bad data (the Q5 fail-loud arm; mirrors the document_highlights case
         in the fk-003 sibling).

      2. fk-002-7..11: VALIDATE CONSTRAINT for each of the five FKs. Each takes a SHARE
         UPDATE EXCLUSIVE lock on its table (concurrent reads/writes proceed), scans
         existing rows once, and on success flips pg_constraint.convalidated to true.
         Idempotent: VALIDATE on an already-validated constraint is a no-op.

    Deploy note (NOT a release gate — the luxe6 freeze gates user-facing PyPI/plugin
    distribution, not applying liquibase migrations to the engine's own PG): safe to
    ship to develop now. On a fresh DB (CI / testcontainers) there are no rows, so
    reconcile is a no-op and VALIDATE trivially passes. On live prod it should be
    applied deliberately with the migration report in hand, because a genuinely-
    orphaned, stub-unsatisfiable row would (correctly) fail the migration loudly.

    Must come after fk-002-collection-registry.xml (the NOT VALID FKs it validates)
    in db.changelog-master.xml.
-->
<databaseChangeLog
    xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog
        http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-4.4.xsd">

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-6-reconcile: fresh idempotent stub-register ────────── -->
    <!--
        Repeats the same five fk-002-0-backfill-stubs SQL statements (inline section
        comments aside), re-run against current data to catch any collection referenced
        by a child table between the 2026-06-11 migration and the P0.2 registration-guard
        deploy. ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING keeps it
        idempotent and safe to re-apply. topic_assignments contributes only non-null,
        non-empty source_collection values (null rows escape the FK).
    -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-6-reconcile" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <comment>
            Re-stub-register catalog_collections rows for every collection referenced by
            chunks_384, chunks_768, chunks_1024, chash_index, and topic_assignments
            (non-null) that is not already registered — the gap-window reconcile that
            precedes VALIDATE. Idempotent (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING).
        </comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
INSERT INTO nexus.catalog_collections (tenant_id, name)
SELECT DISTINCT tenant_id, collection
FROM nexus.chunks_384
ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, name) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO nexus.catalog_collections (tenant_id, name)
SELECT DISTINCT tenant_id, collection
FROM nexus.chunks_768
ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, name) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO nexus.catalog_collections (tenant_id, name)
SELECT DISTINCT tenant_id, collection
FROM nexus.chunks_1024
ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, name) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO nexus.catalog_collections (tenant_id, name)
SELECT DISTINCT tenant_id, physical_collection
FROM nexus.chash_index
ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, name) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO nexus.catalog_collections (tenant_id, name)
SELECT DISTINCT tenant_id, source_collection
FROM nexus.topic_assignments
WHERE source_collection IS NOT NULL
  AND source_collection != ''
ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, name) DO NOTHING;
        </sql>
        <rollback>
            <!-- No rollback: stub rows are inert and may now be referenced. The FKs being
                 validated next own their own DROP CONSTRAINT rollbacks in fk-002. -->
        </rollback>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- nexus-4m6i0.13 (2026-07-10): fk-002-7..11 below were shipped without a
         precondition guard, identically to the ms57z/catalog-013-2 crash-loop class
         (nexus-4m6i0.1) — a bare VALIDATE CONSTRAINT raises a hard Postgres ERROR on
         any box where the constraint is missing, and because a failed changeset never
         commits a DATABASECHANGELOG row, every subsequent boot re-hits the identical
         failure. Each of these five changesets is checksum-immutable once executed
         (already shipped), so the <sql> body cannot change; a whole-changeset
         <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN"> is added instead — verified checksum-neutral
         against the pinned liquibase-core 4.29.0 sources (ChangeSet.generateCheckSum()
         hashes only the <sql>/<changes> body and SqlVisitors, never preConditions), the
         same fact nexus-4m6i0.1 relied on for catalog-013-2. Unlike catalog-013-2 (one
         changeset validating five constraints, IN-list form), each fk-002-N changeset
         here validates exactly ONE constraint, so the single-name
         expectedResult="1" form is the correct shape. A genuine mismatch marks the
         changeset ran (once, never retried) instead of hard-failing; a transient
         connection/query error during the check itself still halts loudly (onError
         defaults to HALT, left unset), so real infra failures are never mistaken for
         "constraint missing."

         NO catalog-013-3-style defensive re-validate changeset is needed here, and
         one deliberately does NOT exist (nexus-4m6i0.13 review): catalog-013-3 is
         load-bearing only because catalog-013-2 is one MONOLITHIC changeset whose
         single IN-list precondition MARK_RANs ALL FIVE of its VALIDATEs when any one
         constraint is missing — collateral damage a follow-up changeset must rescue.
         fk-002-7..11 have no such coupling: each is its own changeset with its own
         single-name precondition, so a missing constraint only ever skips ITS OWN
         VALIDATE and the other four validate independently. (For the record:
         re-VALIDATE of an already-valid constraint would be a fast no-op anyway —
         PostgreSQL skips validation when pg_constraint.convalidated is already true;
         see the ALTER TABLE docs' VALIDATE CONSTRAINT clause / ATExecValidateConstraint
         in src/backend/commands/tablecmds.c — but "harmless" is not a reason to ship
         an inert changeset with a misleading rationale.) -->

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-7: VALIDATE chunks_384_collection_fk ────────────────── -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-7" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">SELECT COUNT(*) FROM pg_constraint WHERE conname = 'chunks_384_collection_fk'</sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>
            VALIDATE chunks_384_collection_fk — retroactively check pre-existing rows now
            that the gap-window reconcile has registered their collections. Guarded by a
            whole-changeset precondition (nexus-4m6i0.13): skips (marks ran, once) instead
            of retrying forever when the constraint is genuinely, persistently missing.
        </comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
ALTER TABLE nexus.chunks_384 VALIDATE CONSTRAINT chunks_384_collection_fk;
        </sql>
        <rollback>
            <!-- VALIDATE cannot be un-done (no INVALIDATE in PG); the constraint itself is
                 dropped by fk-002-1's rollback. No-op here. -->
        </rollback>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-8: VALIDATE chunks_768_collection_fk ────────────────── -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-8" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">SELECT COUNT(*) FROM pg_constraint WHERE conname = 'chunks_768_collection_fk'</sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>VALIDATE chunks_768_collection_fk. Guarded (nexus-4m6i0.13): see fk-002-7's comment.</comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
ALTER TABLE nexus.chunks_768 VALIDATE CONSTRAINT chunks_768_collection_fk;
        </sql>
        <rollback/>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-9: VALIDATE chunks_1024_collection_fk ───────────────── -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-9" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">SELECT COUNT(*) FROM pg_constraint WHERE conname = 'chunks_1024_collection_fk'</sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>VALIDATE chunks_1024_collection_fk. Guarded (nexus-4m6i0.13): see fk-002-7's comment.</comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
ALTER TABLE nexus.chunks_1024 VALIDATE CONSTRAINT chunks_1024_collection_fk;
        </sql>
        <rollback/>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-10: VALIDATE chash_index_collection_fk ──────────────── -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-10" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">SELECT COUNT(*) FROM pg_constraint WHERE conname = 'chash_index_collection_fk'</sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>VALIDATE chash_index_collection_fk (FK on physical_collection). Guarded (nexus-4m6i0.13): see fk-002-7's comment.</comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
ALTER TABLE nexus.chash_index VALIDATE CONSTRAINT chash_index_collection_fk;
        </sql>
        <rollback/>
    </changeSet>

    <!-- ── Changeset fk-002-11: VALIDATE topic_assignments_collection_fk ────────── -->
    <changeSet id="fk-002-11" author="nexus-70r3c.3">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">SELECT COUNT(*) FROM pg_constraint WHERE conname = 'topic_assignments_collection_fk'</sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>
            VALIDATE topic_assignments_collection_fk (FK on source_collection). Null
            source_collection rows are skipped by MATCH SIMPLE; the FK carries ON UPDATE
            CASCADE so a later collection rename propagates automatically. Guarded
            (nexus-4m6i0.13): see fk-002-7's comment.
        </comment>
        <sql splitStatements="true" stripComments="false">
ALTER TABLE nexus.topic_assignments VALIDATE CONSTRAINT topic_assignments_collection_fk;
        </sql>
        <rollback/>
    </changeSet>


</databaseChangeLog>
